{
  "texts": [
    "While there is a trade-off between efficiency and performance, MoFE significantly reduces the size of trainable parameters and training time, demonstrating superiority over other PEFT methods in both training time and task performance.",
    "Furthermore, the transfer of domain expertise from the constituent models enables the creation of multi-domain proficient models by leveraging existing domain experts.",
    "We believe MoFE presents a viable option for resource-constrained environments in real-world scenarios.",
    "To examine how performance shifts with varying numbers of frozen FFN blocks, we use a mediumsized model with four expert models.",
    "TinyLlama serves as the base and expert models, as in previous experiments."
  ]
}